1
00:01:00,143 --> 00:01:01,777
Are you okay?

2
00:01:07,910 --> 00:01:09,544
Beni?

3
00:01:11,488 --> 00:01:13,373
Don't worry.

4
00:01:15,367 --> 00:01:17,209
It's okay.

5
00:01:18,996 --> 00:01:21,339
Everything's going to be fine.

6
00:01:32,510 --> 00:01:34,311
Yun Oh?

7
00:01:35,971 --> 00:01:37,605
Yun Oh.

8
00:01:54,865 --> 00:01:57,083
[KOBAYASHI KANNA]

9
00:01:59,245 --> 00:02:00,829
Hello?

10
00:02:00,829 --> 00:02:04,174
Morning. How did you sleep?

11
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,669
Fine.

12
00:02:06,669 --> 00:02:10,548
I think I got a bit too drunk last night.

13
00:02:10,548 --> 00:02:12,675
Sorry.

14
00:02:12,675 --> 00:02:16,554
Don't worry about it. It's fine.

15
00:02:16,554 --> 00:02:18,764
You don't sound well.

16
00:02:18,764 --> 00:02:20,098
Are you okay?

17
00:02:20,098 --> 00:02:21,975
You're not sick, are you?

18
00:02:21,975 --> 00:02:24,395
No, I'm fine.

19
00:02:24,395 --> 00:02:26,063
It's probably because I just woke up.

20
00:02:26,063 --> 00:02:31,110
You know we have the Japanese
expat meeting at one, right?

21
00:02:31,110 --> 00:02:33,695
It's not too far from the hotel,

22
00:02:33,695 --> 00:02:36,658
so I can meet you in the lobby
30 minutes beforehand.

23
00:02:36,658 --> 00:02:39,410
That early?

24
00:02:39,410 --> 00:02:41,870
Why? Have you made other plans?

25
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:43,956
I'm sorry, Kanna.

26
00:02:43,956 --> 00:02:46,000
Could we cancel the meeting today?

27
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:48,335
Cancel it? Why?

28
00:02:48,335 --> 00:02:52,806
You know how important they are
for the promotion in Korea.

29
00:02:54,049 --> 00:02:55,551
I'm sorry.

30
00:02:55,551 --> 00:02:58,353
I just really need some rest for today.

31
00:02:59,346 --> 00:03:01,398
Okay.

32
00:03:02,933 --> 00:03:04,685
You can take the day off.

33
00:03:04,685 --> 00:03:07,062
Tomorrow's book signing
is more important anyway.

34
00:03:07,062 --> 00:03:09,398
I'll talk to Mr. Lee and smooth things over.

35
00:03:09,398 --> 00:03:11,191
Thanks.

36
00:03:11,191 --> 00:03:12,567
Talk to you later.

37
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:14,202
Bye.

38
00:03:26,582 --> 00:03:28,842
Marry me, Jungo.

39
00:03:30,553 --> 00:03:32,212
Please...

40
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:35,056
come back to me.

41
00:03:47,894 --> 00:03:49,612
I'm sorry.

42
00:03:58,071 --> 00:04:00,407
It's fine.

43
00:04:00,407 --> 00:04:02,750
I'll stop now.

44
00:04:03,702 --> 00:04:07,623
It's been a long day for me, too.

45
00:04:07,623 --> 00:04:10,542
When I heard you were going to Korea,

46
00:04:10,542 --> 00:04:13,136
I was so bothered...

47
00:04:16,673 --> 00:04:19,767
that I couldn't get any sleep
for a few days.

48
00:04:27,851 --> 00:04:30,244
Good night, Jungo.

49
00:04:49,081 --> 00:04:53,468
How was it that we ended up
running into each other like this?

50
00:04:55,045 --> 00:04:59,134
Did we meet each other again for a reason?

51
00:04:59,134 --> 00:05:03,014
Were we given a chance
to pick up where we left off?

52
00:05:03,014 --> 00:05:05,013
Or was it

53
00:05:05,013 --> 00:05:08,308
a chance to prepare ourselves...

54
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:10,818
for the end?

55
00:05:13,647 --> 00:05:15,691
I hope

56
00:05:15,691 --> 00:05:18,777
this isn't the end.

57
00:05:18,777 --> 00:05:25,583
[I HOPE... THIS ISN'T THE END]

58
00:05:30,455 --> 00:05:36,113
[WHAT COMES AFTER LOVE]

59
00:05:56,190 --> 00:05:58,817
[MIN JUN: ARE YOU UP?]

60
00:05:58,817 --> 00:06:01,619
Hong, how are you feeling?

61
00:06:03,697 --> 00:06:07,625
I wish I could make you
breakfast every day.

62
00:06:16,584 --> 00:06:17,828
Hi.

63
00:06:17,836 --> 00:06:18,987
Good morning sir.

64
00:06:18,987 --> 00:06:20,464
How can I help you?

65
00:06:20,464 --> 00:06:22,132
Well...

66
00:06:22,132 --> 00:06:24,760
Could you call a taxi for me, please?

67
00:06:24,760 --> 00:06:28,316
Sure. Do you want a driver who speaks Japanese?

68
00:06:28,316 --> 00:06:30,468
Yes, thank you.

69
00:06:33,810 --> 00:06:36,980
What on earth? Look at this place!

70
00:06:36,980 --> 00:06:38,815
Do you want to try one?

71
00:06:38,815 --> 00:06:40,150
No, thanks.

72
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:43,578
Clean all this up before you go, okay?

73
00:06:45,656 --> 00:06:47,574
- Dad.
- Yes?

74
00:06:47,574 --> 00:06:48,992
Have some breakfast.

75
00:06:48,992 --> 00:06:50,452
I made it myself.

76
00:06:50,452 --> 00:06:52,913
That's so nice of you.

77
00:06:52,913 --> 00:06:55,548
Thanks, sweetie.

78
00:07:03,465 --> 00:07:06,677
- It's good, right?
- What?

79
00:07:06,677 --> 00:07:08,886
Maybe I should open a bakery.

80
00:07:08,886 --> 00:07:11,765
A bakery? Weren't you thinking
about a workshop before?

81
00:07:11,765 --> 00:07:13,225
Candles, was it?

82
00:07:13,225 --> 00:07:15,185
It was a leather goods, Dad.

83
00:07:15,185 --> 00:07:17,229
Leather goods?

84
00:07:17,229 --> 00:07:21,525
There's not much you can do
doing either of those things.

85
00:07:21,525 --> 00:07:23,402
I think baking is the way forward.

86
00:07:23,402 --> 00:07:27,121
I love seeing people enjoy their food.

87
00:07:28,031 --> 00:07:30,242
- Speaking of which--
- Here we go.

88
00:07:30,242 --> 00:07:31,660
Talk to your sister about it.

89
00:07:31,660 --> 00:07:35,421
You know she's the real boss.
I'm just there to look good.

90
00:07:36,957 --> 00:07:38,625
Hong.

91
00:07:38,625 --> 00:07:40,426
You should try one, too.

92
00:07:41,461 --> 00:07:43,505
I'll have one later.

93
00:07:43,505 --> 00:07:45,048
I'm so hungover.

94
00:07:45,048 --> 00:07:48,551
- Wait, were you out with Min Jun?
- Yeah.

95
00:07:48,551 --> 00:07:51,763
Seriously? Why didn't you call me?

96
00:07:51,763 --> 00:07:53,737
Did you all go out after the dress tour?

97
00:07:53,737 --> 00:07:56,685
Which one did you get in the end?

98
00:07:56,685 --> 00:07:58,778
Good morning, Mr. Lee.

99
00:07:59,563 --> 00:08:01,406
He canceled?

100
00:08:02,566 --> 00:08:04,234
I see...

101
00:08:04,234 --> 00:08:07,654
It should be fine.
It's the weekend, after all.

102
00:08:07,654 --> 00:08:10,282
We should let him get some rest.

103
00:08:10,282 --> 00:08:15,037
Sure. Please make sure
you take good care of him.

104
00:08:15,037 --> 00:08:16,754
Okay, thanks.

105
00:08:18,540 --> 00:08:19,958
Who was it?

106
00:08:19,958 --> 00:08:22,419
- Did something happen?
- Oh, that?

107
00:08:22,419 --> 00:08:24,880
The visiting author from Japan
wasn't feeling too well,

108
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:27,758
so he canceled today's itinerary.

109
00:08:27,758 --> 00:08:29,592
Do you mean, Sasae Hikari?

110
00:08:29,592 --> 00:08:31,511
Shouldn't you go to check in on him?

111
00:08:31,511 --> 00:08:33,096
Who, me?

112
00:08:33,096 --> 00:08:35,022
Why would I?

113
00:08:35,022 --> 00:08:38,062
I'm sure Mr. Lee's on top of things.

114
00:08:38,062 --> 00:08:40,437
Wait, before you go.

115
00:08:40,437 --> 00:08:44,690
Do you think
I could borrow your old guitar?

116
00:08:44,690 --> 00:08:45,771
- My guitar?
- Yeah.

117
00:08:45,771 --> 00:08:47,611
What for?

118
00:08:47,611 --> 00:08:51,531
I need a prop for my pastries post online.

119
00:08:51,531 --> 00:08:53,084
It's in the storage closet.

120
00:08:53,084 --> 00:08:54,659
I know that.

121
00:08:54,659 --> 00:08:58,254
But you told me never to touch it.

122
00:09:04,085 --> 00:09:07,214
I can't believe he actually sent it.

123
00:09:07,214 --> 00:09:09,299
Your boyfriend's really something.

124
00:09:09,299 --> 00:09:11,402
You mean, ex-boyfriend.

125
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:14,854
Right, your ex.

126
00:09:16,139 --> 00:09:20,032
I guess this means
that it's really over, right?

127
00:09:24,439 --> 00:09:26,107
Hey, come on.

128
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:27,743
You'll be fine.

129
00:09:27,743 --> 00:09:30,128
Just forget him.

130
00:09:31,071 --> 00:09:32,614
By the way...

131
00:09:32,614 --> 00:09:35,541
Did you get me anything from Japan?

132
00:09:37,702 --> 00:09:40,239
- Is it in here?
- Don't touch that.

133
00:09:40,239 --> 00:09:41,733
Why not?

134
00:09:43,375 --> 00:09:45,009
Just don't.

135
00:09:46,419 --> 00:09:48,179
Don't open it.

136
00:09:49,089 --> 00:09:52,592
It took me a long time to figure it out.

137
00:09:52,592 --> 00:09:55,637
It wasn't Jungo I was trying to forget.

138
00:09:55,637 --> 00:09:59,724
I was trying to forget
the version of myself that loved him.

139
00:09:59,724 --> 00:10:05,321
So, I just sealed away everything about him.

140
00:10:17,034 --> 00:10:18,076
Here you go.

141
00:10:18,076 --> 00:10:21,912
Thanks. I'll make sure
to put it back right after I'm done.

142
00:10:54,612 --> 00:10:57,533
Excuse me, sir.

143
00:10:57,533 --> 00:10:58,575
Yes?

144
00:10:58,575 --> 00:11:03,747
I haven't been there myself,
so I'm not entirely sure,

145
00:11:03,747 --> 00:11:06,924
but I think this lake
you're going to is pretty big.

146
00:11:09,711 --> 00:11:15,216
I'd like to go where I can see
the path around the lake.

147
00:11:15,216 --> 00:11:17,761
I'm sorry for being difficult.

148
00:11:17,761 --> 00:11:19,346
Don't worry about it.

149
00:11:19,346 --> 00:11:21,773
It's just part of my job.

150
00:11:42,828 --> 00:11:44,746
Isn't that too much pruning?

151
00:11:44,746 --> 00:11:46,748
You can be so cruel.

152
00:11:46,748 --> 00:11:50,210
It's got to be done if we want
to see a full bloom next year.

153
00:11:50,210 --> 00:11:53,922
Did you think raising something
was just fun and games?

154
00:11:53,922 --> 00:11:57,843
I'm sure it isn't,
and I'm sure kids are no different.

155
00:11:57,843 --> 00:12:01,430
Well, aren't you smart?
Push that one over, will you?

156
00:12:01,430 --> 00:12:03,140
Sure.

157
00:12:03,140 --> 00:12:06,526
No, don't drag it. Lift it up.

158
00:12:08,395 --> 00:12:10,063
How's that?

159
00:12:10,063 --> 00:12:12,190
That's good. All set.

160
00:12:12,190 --> 00:12:15,694
Have you found a venue yet?

161
00:12:15,694 --> 00:12:17,404
Min Jun is looking into it.

162
00:12:17,404 --> 00:12:20,907
Don't be too picky about it.
It's not like you're looking for a house.

163
00:12:20,907 --> 00:12:22,743
Just go with any decent-looking one.

164
00:12:22,743 --> 00:12:24,995
He must be busy as well.

165
00:12:24,995 --> 00:12:26,629
Okay.

166
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:30,794
- What's the matter?
- What?

167
00:12:30,794 --> 00:12:33,128
Did you two have a fight?

168
00:12:33,128 --> 00:12:35,138
No, we didn't.

169
00:12:37,216 --> 00:12:40,686
It's so cold. I'm going inside to warm up.

170
00:12:44,348 --> 00:12:46,975
What's gotten into you?

171
00:12:46,975 --> 00:12:50,228
I used to do this all the time
when I was little.

172
00:12:50,228 --> 00:12:51,772
You did.

173
00:12:51,772 --> 00:12:54,608
Back when you used to listen to me.

174
00:12:54,608 --> 00:12:58,236
You were so lovable back then.

175
00:12:58,236 --> 00:12:59,947
So, am I not anymore?

176
00:12:59,947 --> 00:13:02,115
Exactly. Not in the slightest.

177
00:13:02,115 --> 00:13:05,410
That's why I want Min Jun
to take you with him.

178
00:13:05,410 --> 00:13:07,746
Do you like him that much?

179
00:13:07,746 --> 00:13:10,207
Of course, I do. He's amazing.

180
00:13:10,207 --> 00:13:11,667
He's kind and steadfast.

181
00:13:11,667 --> 00:13:13,826
He's been that way since he was a kid.

182
00:13:13,826 --> 00:13:17,013
Do you have any idea
how much of a catch he is?

183
00:13:17,714 --> 00:13:21,225
Yeah, I know. He really is amazing.

184
00:13:22,803 --> 00:13:24,805
Listen.

185
00:13:24,805 --> 00:13:28,934
You're not supposed to marry someone you love.

186
00:13:28,934 --> 00:13:31,778
You need a good person to be your spouse.

187
00:13:37,693 --> 00:13:40,779
Jungo and I used to talk
about getting married.

188
00:13:40,779 --> 00:13:45,075
But it wasn't the same kind of marriage
that my mom talked about.

189
00:13:45,075 --> 00:13:47,326
Now that I think about it,

190
00:13:47,326 --> 00:13:49,121
I don't think marriage is the right word.

191
00:13:49,121 --> 00:13:53,667
We just wanted to be with each other forever.

192
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:56,962
That was what we wanted
to say to each other.

193
00:13:56,962 --> 00:13:59,847
[ICHIRO'S RAMEN]

194
00:14:00,924 --> 00:14:02,718
Hey, everyone!

195
00:14:02,718 --> 00:14:04,928
- Welcome.
- Hello, Nozomi.

196
00:14:04,928 --> 00:14:06,096
Good evening, Nozomi!

197
00:14:06,096 --> 00:14:08,398
[DEAR MS. CHOI HONG]

198
00:14:09,224 --> 00:14:11,934
What's... this?

199
00:14:11,934 --> 00:14:13,684
It's a wedding invitation.

200
00:14:13,684 --> 00:14:15,898
Oh, my god!

201
00:14:15,898 --> 00:14:17,106
Boss!

202
00:14:17,106 --> 00:14:18,775
I can't believe this.

203
00:14:18,775 --> 00:14:20,026
You can't be serious?

204
00:14:20,026 --> 00:14:22,029
This is a miracle!

205
00:14:22,029 --> 00:14:24,573
What was it? Ten proposals?

206
00:14:24,573 --> 00:14:31,704
I can't believe she finally said "yes"!

207
00:14:31,704 --> 00:14:32,956
All right, everyone.

208
00:14:32,956 --> 00:14:34,541
First things first.

209
00:14:34,541 --> 00:14:39,512
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

210
00:14:41,632 --> 00:14:44,475
- That's so good!
- That hit the spot.

211
00:14:50,599 --> 00:14:52,267
What's got into you?

212
00:14:52,267 --> 00:14:54,102
What's wrong?

213
00:14:54,102 --> 00:14:56,104
It's nothing.

214
00:14:56,104 --> 00:14:57,564
- I just...
- What's the matter?

215
00:14:57,564 --> 00:15:01,442
Are you sad that I'm getting married?

216
00:15:01,442 --> 00:15:05,906
I'm sorry, but I don't feel
the same way about you.

217
00:15:05,906 --> 00:15:08,033
You should've told him sooner.

218
00:15:08,033 --> 00:15:10,285
I could've got away then.

219
00:15:10,285 --> 00:15:11,703
Too bad.

220
00:15:11,703 --> 00:15:14,297
No, it's not like that.

221
00:15:15,248 --> 00:15:17,175
It's just that...

222
00:15:18,210 --> 00:15:22,004
I don't have any family or friends in Japan.

223
00:15:22,004 --> 00:15:23,715
So, I always felt a bit lonely.

224
00:15:23,715 --> 00:15:25,516
But...

225
00:15:26,176 --> 00:15:28,220
But you've been so good to me

226
00:15:28,220 --> 00:15:30,930
and even invited me to your wedding

227
00:15:30,930 --> 00:15:33,517
as if we were family.

228
00:15:33,517 --> 00:15:35,185
All right.

229
00:15:35,185 --> 00:15:40,023
To celebrate Hong becoming
a part of our family,

230
00:15:40,023 --> 00:15:41,483
how about another drink?

231
00:15:41,483 --> 00:15:43,820
That sounds good.

232
00:15:44,527 --> 00:15:47,197
- Jjan!
- "Jjan"?

233
00:15:47,197 --> 00:15:49,741
Yeah, Hong taught me this.

234
00:15:49,741 --> 00:15:52,953
That's how you say "cheers" in Korean.

235
00:15:52,953 --> 00:15:55,121
- Really?
- Yeah.

236
00:15:55,121 --> 00:15:57,666
- Ready?
- Jjan!

237
00:15:57,666 --> 00:16:00,176
- Jjan!
- Jjan!

238
00:16:07,477 --> 00:16:08,719
What's this?

239
00:16:08,719 --> 00:16:11,054
I got invited to a wedding.

240
00:16:11,054 --> 00:16:14,349
Boss is finally getting married.

241
00:16:14,349 --> 00:16:16,685
Really?

242
00:16:16,685 --> 00:16:18,895
He wanted you to come as well.

243
00:16:18,895 --> 00:16:20,464
- Did he?
- Yeah.

244
00:16:20,464 --> 00:16:23,941
And he asked if you were allergic to anything.

245
00:16:23,941 --> 00:16:25,736
I think that's so considerate.

246
00:16:25,736 --> 00:16:29,205
People don't usually ask that in Korea.

247
00:16:34,161 --> 00:16:36,212
You're coming, right?

248
00:16:39,333 --> 00:16:40,334
I'll think about it.

249
00:16:40,334 --> 00:16:42,865
Hey, don't be like that! You should come.

250
00:16:42,865 --> 00:16:45,212
Come on, let's go.

251
00:16:46,089 --> 00:16:47,465
What's the matter?

252
00:16:47,465 --> 00:16:49,343
Do you need to go to work?

253
00:16:49,343 --> 00:16:51,511
I mean, that's one reason...

254
00:16:51,511 --> 00:16:53,305
You've got nothing to worry about.

255
00:16:53,305 --> 00:16:56,160
I've already prepared a gift for them.

256
00:16:56,160 --> 00:16:57,392
A gift?

257
00:16:57,392 --> 00:16:59,186
You'll see what it is on the day.

258
00:16:59,186 --> 00:17:01,571
That's another thing to look forward to!

259
00:17:03,899 --> 00:17:06,360
What are weddings like in Japan, anyway?

260
00:17:06,360 --> 00:17:09,287
I've only been to weddings in Korea.

261
00:17:10,405 --> 00:17:12,783
Well...

262
00:17:12,783 --> 00:17:16,252
I'm sure they're both pretty similar.

263
00:17:18,789 --> 00:17:21,833
It's totally different from a Korean wedding.

264
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:23,794
It's totally different there.

265
00:17:23,794 --> 00:17:25,462
Right?

266
00:17:25,462 --> 00:17:28,048
Jungo won't ever talk about these things.

267
00:17:28,048 --> 00:17:29,465
It's so frustrating.

268
00:17:29,465 --> 00:17:31,467
He probably doesn't want you
feeling pressured.

269
00:17:31,467 --> 00:17:33,094
What are you talking about?

270
00:17:33,094 --> 00:17:34,679
Don't get me started.

271
00:17:34,679 --> 00:17:37,307
I was totally flustered
when my cousin got married there.

272
00:17:37,307 --> 00:17:41,819
First of all, the cash gift there starts
at the equivalent of 300,000 won.

273
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:45,148
Seriously? That's so much.

274
00:17:45,148 --> 00:17:48,526
That's why they only invite
close family and friends.

275
00:17:48,526 --> 00:17:50,278
And if you said yes to the invite,

276
00:17:50,278 --> 00:17:52,571
you can't not show up like we do in Korea.

277
00:17:52,571 --> 00:17:53,907
You have to be there in person.

278
00:17:53,907 --> 00:17:55,950
I heard it's really rude not to go.

279
00:17:55,950 --> 00:17:57,410
I see...

280
00:17:57,410 --> 00:17:59,579
Hey, start writing this down.

281
00:17:59,579 --> 00:18:03,041
You need to buy a special envelope for the cash gift, too.

282
00:18:03,041 --> 00:18:05,418
- A special envelope?
- That's right.

283
00:18:05,418 --> 00:18:07,754
It's so different over there.

284
00:18:07,754 --> 00:18:09,673
You're right.

285
00:18:09,673 --> 00:18:11,257
Oh, right.

286
00:18:11,257 --> 00:18:12,509
When are you getting your hair done?

287
00:18:12,509 --> 00:18:13,760
Why would I need it done?

288
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:16,012
The guests go all out in Japan.

289
00:18:16,012 --> 00:18:19,391
They show up in sparkly dresses with perfect hair.

290
00:18:19,391 --> 00:18:21,351
And the men put on clean-cut suits.

291
00:18:21,351 --> 00:18:23,216
Have you decided what you'll wear?

292
00:18:23,216 --> 00:18:24,521
Clothes?

293
00:18:24,521 --> 00:18:26,523
Oh, no.

294
00:18:26,523 --> 00:18:28,561
You don't have any.

295
00:18:49,963 --> 00:18:52,008
Ji Hui told me something.

296
00:18:52,008 --> 00:18:53,302
What did she say?

297
00:18:53,302 --> 00:18:57,679
Apparently, I need to dress nicely
for weddings in Japan.

298
00:18:57,679 --> 00:19:00,396
That sounds about right.

299
00:19:02,976 --> 00:19:05,862
Have you thought
about the kind of wedding you'd like?

300
00:19:08,398 --> 00:19:10,483
I think...

301
00:19:10,483 --> 00:19:13,695
I'd prefer to have a small wedding.

302
00:19:13,695 --> 00:19:17,574
Just like the one in About Time.

303
00:19:17,574 --> 00:19:20,826
Then, I guess you'll also need
some rain in the middle of it.

304
00:19:20,826 --> 00:19:22,120
Of course.

305
00:19:22,120 --> 00:19:24,038
With umbrellas turning inside out!

306
00:19:24,038 --> 00:19:28,376
That sudden downpour was
what made the wedding so special.

307
00:19:28,376 --> 00:19:32,756
I'd invite Ji Hui and everyone from Ichiro's Ramen.

308
00:19:32,756 --> 00:19:34,799
I'd like to ask your father

309
00:19:34,799 --> 00:19:38,178
to perform with his band, too.

310
00:19:38,178 --> 00:19:40,646
I bet he'd be more than happy to help.

311
00:19:43,141 --> 00:19:44,922
But...

312
00:19:44,922 --> 00:19:46,896
I don't think my mom would come

313
00:19:46,896 --> 00:19:49,822
if I got married in Japan.

314
00:19:51,316 --> 00:19:54,454
Is she still ignoring your calls?

315
00:19:55,695 --> 00:19:57,030
Don't worry.

316
00:19:57,030 --> 00:19:59,623
I'm sure she'll get over it eventually.

317
00:20:28,812 --> 00:20:31,572
It's so pretty.

318
00:20:36,695 --> 00:20:38,329
Yun Oh?

319
00:20:41,282 --> 00:20:43,117
- Welcome.
- Hello.

320
00:20:43,117 --> 00:20:44,160
Hello.

321
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:45,412
Would it...

322
00:20:45,412 --> 00:20:48,464
Would it be possible to try on that dress?

323
00:20:49,374 --> 00:20:51,376
No, Yun Oh. It's fine.

324
00:20:51,376 --> 00:20:53,545
Of course, you can.

325
00:20:53,545 --> 00:20:58,689
We'll start by taking your measurements.

326
00:20:58,689 --> 00:21:00,907
This way, please.

327
00:21:04,264 --> 00:21:06,774
See you in a bit.

328
00:21:19,779 --> 00:21:21,530
Are you ready?

329
00:21:21,530 --> 00:21:22,657
Pardon?

330
00:21:22,657 --> 00:21:27,203
Remember to give her a big smile, okay?

331
00:21:27,203 --> 00:21:30,714
- Oh, of course.
- Okay, then. Here she comes.

332
00:22:23,010 --> 00:22:24,811
You look...

333
00:22:25,804 --> 00:22:27,897
so beautiful.

334
00:22:29,432 --> 00:22:33,812
That's exactly what we like to hear.

335
00:22:33,812 --> 00:22:35,856
I think the best compliments

336
00:22:35,856 --> 00:22:39,617
come from being genuinely sincere
about your feelings.

337
00:22:52,998 --> 00:22:54,791
- Hey.
- Hi.

338
00:22:54,791 --> 00:22:56,126
Here you go.

339
00:22:56,126 --> 00:22:58,336
Thanks. I'll take good care of it.

340
00:22:58,336 --> 00:22:59,713
Do you have an interview?

341
00:22:59,713 --> 00:23:03,717
No. I was just invited
to Hong's friend's wedding.

342
00:23:03,717 --> 00:23:04,801
How's she doing?

343
00:23:04,801 --> 00:23:07,094
- She's well.
- I almost forgot.

344
00:23:07,094 --> 00:23:11,182
I heard Sato was looking for someone
to do some work for him.

345
00:23:11,182 --> 00:23:12,475
Are you interested?

346
00:23:12,475 --> 00:23:15,938
You've been looking for a publishing job, right?

347
00:23:15,938 --> 00:23:19,107
Sato's looking for people?

348
00:23:19,107 --> 00:23:20,734
I'd love that.

349
00:23:20,734 --> 00:23:22,444
You should meet up with him tomorrow.

350
00:23:22,444 --> 00:23:24,863
He seemed to be in a hurry.

351
00:23:24,863 --> 00:23:26,448
You have his number, right?

352
00:23:26,448 --> 00:23:28,575
I do. I'll give him a call. Thanks.

353
00:23:28,575 --> 00:23:30,960
- I'm off. Thanks again.
- No problem!

354
00:23:42,714 --> 00:23:46,684
- Do you know where it is, Yoshino?
- Check the top shelf on the right.

355
00:23:48,178 --> 00:23:50,187
Over here, Aoki.

356
00:23:56,143 --> 00:23:58,563
Thank you for meeting with me today, sir.

357
00:23:58,563 --> 00:24:00,106
How's the writing coming along?

358
00:24:00,106 --> 00:24:02,150
I haven't been writing much recently.

359
00:24:02,150 --> 00:24:03,985
You always had a lot of potential.

360
00:24:03,985 --> 00:24:07,405
Especially out of your classmates.

361
00:24:07,405 --> 00:24:09,706
Thank you very much.

362
00:24:10,366 --> 00:24:13,453
I'll save the rest
of my nagging for later.

363
00:24:13,453 --> 00:24:14,703
Can you start today?

364
00:24:14,703 --> 00:24:17,081
We just had two people quit.

365
00:24:17,081 --> 00:24:19,383
We're in a real bind.

366
00:24:20,042 --> 00:24:21,544
Do you need me to start today?

367
00:24:21,544 --> 00:24:23,379
You don't want to?

368
00:24:23,379 --> 00:24:26,974
No, it's not that. It's just...

369
00:24:46,778 --> 00:24:48,990
- Congratulations on the wedding.
- Thank you for coming.

370
00:24:48,990 --> 00:24:51,900
- Thank you.
- Please go on in.

371
00:24:51,900 --> 00:24:54,620
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

372
00:24:54,620 --> 00:24:56,671
Thank you for coming.

373
00:25:03,252 --> 00:25:05,137
[MR. AOKI JUNGO]

374
00:25:07,381 --> 00:25:09,516
[MS. CHOI HONG]

375
00:25:26,109 --> 00:25:27,693
- Hong!
- Hey!

376
00:25:27,693 --> 00:25:30,287
- Hello.
- Good to see you.

377
00:25:31,155 --> 00:25:33,075
Isn't Jungo coming today?

378
00:25:33,075 --> 00:25:36,872
He'll be here soon.
He had to stop by for an interview.

379
00:25:36,872 --> 00:25:39,580
Everything set for today's special performance?

380
00:25:39,580 --> 00:25:43,611
No. I've never performed
at a wedding before.

381
00:25:43,611 --> 00:25:45,802
I'm so nervous.

382
00:25:46,672 --> 00:25:47,881
Don't worry about it.

383
00:25:47,881 --> 00:25:51,049
Everyone's going to be blown away
if you do what you did at rehearsals.

384
00:25:51,049 --> 00:25:52,635
- He's right.
- You'll be fine.

385
00:25:52,635 --> 00:25:54,470
I'm not sure about that.

386
00:25:54,470 --> 00:25:58,056
- You'll be fine!
- Seriously, don't worry.

387
00:25:58,056 --> 00:26:00,935
Ladies and gentlemen, thank you very much

388
00:26:00,935 --> 00:26:03,938
for taking the time
out of your busy schedules

389
00:26:03,938 --> 00:26:07,650
to attend the wedding
of Mr. Nitta Ichiro and Ms. Gato Nozomi.

390
00:26:07,650 --> 00:26:11,654
The groom and bride will soon
make their entrance.

391
00:26:11,654 --> 00:26:13,948
When you see them,

392
00:26:13,948 --> 00:26:17,244
please welcome them
with a warm round of applause.

393
00:26:17,244 --> 00:26:21,915
Now, I'd like to ask you all
to direct your attention to the back.

394
00:26:21,915 --> 00:26:24,925
Please welcome the bride and groom!

395
00:26:32,885 --> 00:26:34,970
Boss, you look so cool!

396
00:26:34,970 --> 00:26:36,980
Try to relax a little!

397
00:26:40,141 --> 00:26:43,770
This draft needs
to be proofread by seven o'clock.

398
00:26:43,770 --> 00:26:46,113
- I got it.
- Thanks.

399
00:27:04,999 --> 00:27:08,093
[MISSED CALL, BENI]

400
00:27:10,454 --> 00:27:14,758
Next, we have a special surprise
for the bride and groom.

401
00:27:14,758 --> 00:27:19,305
We hope it'll be a pleasant surprise
to mark this special occasion.

402
00:27:19,305 --> 00:27:20,681
Actually,

403
00:27:20,681 --> 00:27:23,476
we knew that the groom had kept
a secret crush from the bride,

404
00:27:23,476 --> 00:27:25,186
so we tried to invite TWICE to join us today.

405
00:27:25,186 --> 00:27:27,648
Hey, shut it!

406
00:27:27,648 --> 00:27:31,441
- I guess his angry response confirms it.
- Come on.

407
00:27:31,441 --> 00:27:33,903
I think that's enough joking around.

408
00:27:33,903 --> 00:27:36,740
Joining us on the stage is
Ichiro's Ramen's very own K-pop star.

409
00:27:36,740 --> 00:27:38,867
Please welcome Ms. Choi Hong!

410
00:27:38,867 --> 00:27:42,211
Please give her a big round of applause!

411
00:27:45,153 --> 00:27:46,916
Ichiro and Nozomi.

412
00:27:46,916 --> 00:27:49,085
Congratulations on your wedding.

413
00:27:49,085 --> 00:27:50,878
I might not be very good,

414
00:27:50,878 --> 00:27:54,264
so I'd appreciate it
if you'd listen with kindness.

415
00:28:54,692 --> 00:28:57,528
You scared me.

416
00:28:57,528 --> 00:28:59,238
Were you taking a photo?

417
00:28:59,238 --> 00:29:00,956
Yes.

418
00:29:07,664 --> 00:29:09,465
Yun Oh!

419
00:31:18,369 --> 00:31:20,003
Beni...

420
00:31:21,381 --> 00:31:23,056
Are you okay?

421
00:31:26,011 --> 00:31:28,388
The publisher I interviewed with

422
00:31:28,388 --> 00:31:32,058
asked me to start today.

423
00:31:32,058 --> 00:31:34,019
I see.

424
00:31:34,019 --> 00:31:36,070
Why did it have to be today?

425
00:31:37,564 --> 00:31:41,151
I've always wanted to work there.

426
00:31:41,151 --> 00:31:43,369
I really couldn't help it.

427
00:31:57,250 --> 00:31:58,968
What's this?

428
00:32:00,628 --> 00:32:02,763
Your thank-you gift from the wedding.

429
00:32:04,132 --> 00:32:08,310
I'm tired. I'm going to bed.

430
00:32:09,680 --> 00:32:12,107
You shouldn't have taken these.

431
00:32:12,724 --> 00:32:14,358
What was that?

432
00:32:16,686 --> 00:32:19,022
It's just...

433
00:32:19,022 --> 00:32:21,815
I didn't give them any congratulatory money.

434
00:32:21,815 --> 00:32:24,194
It'd be rude of me to accept a thank-you gift.

435
00:32:24,194 --> 00:32:26,029
If you're so well-versed in manners,

436
00:32:26,029 --> 00:32:28,365
why did you not show up at all?

437
00:32:28,365 --> 00:32:29,574
But this was...

438
00:32:29,574 --> 00:32:31,950
Didn't you say you'd try to make the time?

439
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:33,912
I told you that I'd try.

440
00:32:33,912 --> 00:32:35,705
I didn't say I'd definitely be there.

441
00:32:35,705 --> 00:32:38,667
You could've just said
that you didn't want to go.

442
00:32:38,667 --> 00:32:39,751
What?

443
00:32:39,751 --> 00:32:41,878
You shouldn't have said anything

444
00:32:41,878 --> 00:32:44,388
if this was how it was going to be.

445
00:32:51,429 --> 00:32:52,722
Wait, Beni...

446
00:32:52,722 --> 00:32:54,773
Leave me alone.

447
00:33:16,788 --> 00:33:21,008
It didn't take very long for me to realize...

448
00:33:22,502 --> 00:33:25,012
that everlasting love didn't exist.

449
00:37:25,704 --> 00:37:28,373
Here we go, Min Jun.

450
00:37:28,373 --> 00:37:29,666
Great. Forehand, now.

451
00:37:29,666 --> 00:37:31,376
You need to see the ball through.

452
00:37:31,376 --> 00:37:34,303
There you go. Backhand, now.

453
00:37:37,632 --> 00:37:39,266
Are you all right?

454
00:37:40,176 --> 00:37:41,811
Hey.

455
00:37:43,138 --> 00:37:45,182
Let's call it a day.

456
00:37:45,182 --> 00:37:47,692
I feel like I'm about to throw up.

457
00:37:52,272 --> 00:37:55,191
- Have you found a house yet?
- Well...

458
00:37:55,191 --> 00:37:58,111
Not yet. Hong's been busy, too.

459
00:37:58,111 --> 00:38:00,030
How is she doing?

460
00:38:00,030 --> 00:38:01,948
- Why do you ask?
- Oh, no reason.

461
00:38:01,948 --> 00:38:06,244
I just remember how my wife was
before the wedding.

462
00:38:06,244 --> 00:38:08,580
It took her a few years
to tell me how she felt.

463
00:38:08,580 --> 00:38:12,508
She was scared at the thought
of actually getting married.

464
00:38:13,960 --> 00:38:17,130
Your wife is the bravest person I know.

465
00:38:17,130 --> 00:38:18,340
I doubt she was scared.

466
00:38:18,340 --> 00:38:20,091
I know, right?

467
00:38:20,091 --> 00:38:23,136
I was so nervous until the night before.

468
00:38:23,136 --> 00:38:28,399
Just remember not to let your guard down
until you walk down that aisle.

469
00:38:38,610 --> 00:38:40,904
Hong, you haven't forgotten about tomorrow, right?

470
00:38:40,904 --> 00:38:43,448
Get a good night's sleep. See you tomorrow.

471
00:38:43,448 --> 00:38:46,542
[ALL RIGHT]

472
00:38:57,671 --> 00:38:59,346
Hey, Lightning.

473
00:39:00,507 --> 00:39:02,592
You know, right?

474
00:39:02,592 --> 00:39:05,853
How bad my memory is.

475
00:39:10,642 --> 00:39:14,270
But why can't I forget

476
00:39:14,270 --> 00:39:16,947
about Jungo?

477
00:39:24,989 --> 00:39:27,868
Why do you think that is?

478
00:39:27,868 --> 00:39:31,788
What are you doing
sitting outside in the cold?

479
00:39:31,788 --> 00:39:34,131
What do you want?

480
00:39:35,667 --> 00:39:37,377
Here.

481
00:39:37,377 --> 00:39:39,053
What's this?

482
00:39:39,796 --> 00:39:42,340
I found it in your guitar case.

483
00:39:42,340 --> 00:39:44,843
I assumed you already had
a lot on your mind,

484
00:39:44,843 --> 00:39:47,220
so I wasn't sure
if I should give it to you.

485
00:39:47,220 --> 00:39:50,147
But I couldn't just pretend like I didn't see it.

486
00:39:51,975 --> 00:39:53,810
It's fine.

487
00:39:53,810 --> 00:39:56,070
Aren't you going to read it?

488
00:40:05,363 --> 00:40:07,947
Really? Already?

489
00:40:07,947 --> 00:40:10,918
Yes, I understand.
We'll be there as soon as we can.

490
00:40:10,918 --> 00:40:12,495
Thank you.

491
00:40:12,495 --> 00:40:13,872
We did it!

492
00:40:13,872 --> 00:40:16,289
There's a huge line outside already!

493
00:40:16,289 --> 00:40:18,125
Are you serious?

494
00:40:18,125 --> 00:40:20,376
The book signing's
not for another four hours.

495
00:40:20,376 --> 00:40:23,131
- That's great news!
- Amazing.

496
00:40:23,131 --> 00:40:24,765
I almost forgot.

497
00:40:28,176 --> 00:40:29,554
Ms. Hong.

498
00:40:29,554 --> 00:40:33,224
I heard it was Mr. Sasae's birthday.

499
00:40:33,224 --> 00:40:34,726
Oh, is it?

500
00:40:34,726 --> 00:40:37,076
What should we get for his gift?

501
00:40:37,076 --> 00:40:38,711
Pardon?

502
00:40:39,481 --> 00:40:42,400
Why are you asking me?

503
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:45,236
I heard from Mr. Lee that you spent some time

504
00:40:45,236 --> 00:40:47,072
- studying in Japan--
- Mr. Yun.

505
00:40:47,072 --> 00:40:50,291
How are those two things related?

506
00:40:51,868 --> 00:40:54,003
I'll try to figure it out on my own.

507
00:41:13,306 --> 00:41:15,892
Please come in.

508
00:41:15,892 --> 00:41:19,479
Ah, I'm so full.

509
00:41:19,479 --> 00:41:22,941
Bulgogi is going to be
my go-to meal from now on.

510
00:41:22,941 --> 00:41:24,567
And it was even better today

511
00:41:24,567 --> 00:41:28,204
because Beni treated me.

512
00:41:28,988 --> 00:41:32,992
Dad, you had three servings by yourself.

513
00:41:32,992 --> 00:41:35,743
Do you know how hard she worked
to pay for that meal?

514
00:41:35,743 --> 00:41:38,915
- Come on. I can afford that much.
- Right!

515
00:41:38,915 --> 00:41:41,418
And I couldn't help it because it was so good.

516
00:41:41,418 --> 00:41:45,463
Don't worry. I'll treat you on
your birthday next year, too.

517
00:41:45,463 --> 00:41:47,048
Really?

518
00:41:47,048 --> 00:41:49,259
I'm so happy today.

519
00:41:49,259 --> 00:41:51,177
Thank you, Beni.

520
00:41:51,177 --> 00:41:53,638
I should be thanking you.

521
00:41:53,638 --> 00:41:55,390
Jungo and I wouldn't be together

522
00:41:55,390 --> 00:41:57,650
if it wasn't for you.

523
00:42:19,789 --> 00:42:20,999
Is this...

524
00:42:20,999 --> 00:42:23,001
your grandmother?

525
00:42:23,001 --> 00:42:24,635
That's right.

526
00:42:26,046 --> 00:42:30,633
She raised Jungo when he was young.

527
00:42:30,633 --> 00:42:33,060
After his mother ran away from home.

528
00:42:47,276 --> 00:42:49,486
What a unique-looking cake.

529
00:42:49,486 --> 00:42:51,864
Don't kids usually have cakes

530
00:42:51,864 --> 00:42:56,126
that are decorated with fruits
or cartoon characters?

531
00:42:57,410 --> 00:43:01,484
My grandmother really liked Mont Blancs.

532
00:43:01,484 --> 00:43:02,624
A Mont Blanc cake

533
00:43:02,624 --> 00:43:07,045
is supposed to look like
a snowy mountain top in the Alps.

534
00:43:07,045 --> 00:43:08,542
The Alps?

535
00:43:08,542 --> 00:43:11,049
- The mountain range?
- Yeah.

536
00:43:11,049 --> 00:43:15,303
She always wanted to go to the Alps.

537
00:43:15,303 --> 00:43:19,140
But she had weak legs since she was a child.

538
00:43:19,140 --> 00:43:22,519
She loved to watch documentaries
on mountain trekking.

539
00:43:22,519 --> 00:43:25,863
That's why she always bought me
a Mont Blanc cake.

540
00:43:34,155 --> 00:43:35,789
Jungo!

541
00:43:39,889 --> 00:43:40,954
Look!

542
00:43:40,954 --> 00:43:42,135
Pardon?

543
00:43:42,135 --> 00:43:44,173
Did you say 5,200 yen?

544
00:43:45,917 --> 00:43:47,335
Beni.

545
00:43:47,335 --> 00:43:50,338
I'm still full after that bulgogi.

546
00:43:50,338 --> 00:43:52,340
I don't think I can have anything else.

547
00:43:52,340 --> 00:43:54,391
Let's have it next time.

548
00:43:55,844 --> 00:43:59,097
Can we buy it by the piece?

549
00:43:59,097 --> 00:44:00,515
I'm sorry.

550
00:44:00,515 --> 00:44:03,101
We don't sell the Mont Blanc by the piece.

551
00:44:03,101 --> 00:44:06,480
Cutting it ruins the shape.

552
00:44:06,480 --> 00:44:08,898
I see.

553
00:44:08,898 --> 00:44:12,535
Shall we get something else, then?

554
00:44:15,447 --> 00:44:18,074
Beni, I'm really full right now.

555
00:44:18,074 --> 00:44:19,200
What was it?

556
00:44:19,200 --> 00:44:20,452
I'm fool.

557
00:44:20,452 --> 00:44:21,828
- Are you full?
- Yeah.

558
00:44:21,828 --> 00:44:24,080
- Really?
- I'm sure.

559
00:44:24,080 --> 00:44:26,082
Let's come back another time.

560
00:44:26,082 --> 00:44:29,593
I really wanted to spoil you today...

561
00:44:30,963 --> 00:44:34,682
- We'll come back at another time.
- No problem. Please do.

562
00:44:42,599 --> 00:44:46,394
I had such a nice day today.

563
00:44:46,394 --> 00:44:50,023
It was so nice to hear stories about you.

564
00:44:50,023 --> 00:44:52,734
- Stories about me?
- Yeah.

565
00:44:52,734 --> 00:44:57,371
You usually don't talk about yourself.

566
00:44:58,656 --> 00:45:01,034
I don't?

567
00:45:01,034 --> 00:45:05,087
Oh, come on. You know it's true.

568
00:45:06,373 --> 00:45:11,461
We can't express all our feelings by just speaking,

569
00:45:11,461 --> 00:45:14,847
but some things need to be said for it to be known.

570
00:45:16,049 --> 00:45:18,851
You're right, but...

571
00:45:20,720 --> 00:45:22,889
But I just find it difficult.

572
00:45:22,889 --> 00:45:26,101
It's hard for me to find
the right way to say things.

573
00:45:26,101 --> 00:45:28,728
As long as you're sincere,

574
00:45:28,728 --> 00:45:31,523
your honest feelings

575
00:45:31,523 --> 00:45:34,408
are eventually going to be felt.

576
00:45:35,251 --> 00:45:37,451
Even still.

577
00:45:37,451 --> 00:45:39,836
It'd be nice if you could tell me.

578
00:45:40,657 --> 00:45:43,660
I may already know how you feel,

579
00:45:43,660 --> 00:45:46,955
but it's nice to hear you say it out loud.

580
00:45:46,955 --> 00:45:48,589
Like what?

581
00:45:50,292 --> 00:45:52,252
"I love you."

582
00:45:52,252 --> 00:45:54,386
That could be one of them.

583
00:45:59,676 --> 00:46:02,561
That's a hard one.

584
00:46:04,180 --> 00:46:06,641
But instead,

585
00:46:06,641 --> 00:46:08,435
I'm going to write a novel

586
00:46:08,435 --> 00:46:12,272
about how I feel about you one day.

587
00:46:12,272 --> 00:46:14,733
- Really?
- Yes.

588
00:46:14,733 --> 00:46:16,575
I promise.

589
00:46:17,944 --> 00:46:20,155
A novel about me...

590
00:46:20,155 --> 00:46:22,331
I can't wait to read it.

591
00:46:34,878 --> 00:46:38,139
"One star for memories

592
00:46:39,090 --> 00:46:42,093
and one for love.

593
00:46:42,093 --> 00:46:45,513
One star for loneliness

594
00:46:45,513 --> 00:46:48,516
and one for yearning.

595
00:46:48,516 --> 00:46:52,979
- One star for poetry..."
- "One star for poetry..."

596
00:46:52,979 --> 00:46:55,281
When did you memorize that?

597
00:46:57,233 --> 00:46:59,944
Whenever you recited that part,

598
00:46:59,944 --> 00:47:02,572
I don't know why,

599
00:47:02,572 --> 00:47:04,498
but I really liked it.

600
00:47:07,952 --> 00:47:11,706
"One star for poetry..."

601
00:47:11,706 --> 00:47:13,632
Did you know?

602
00:47:14,250 --> 00:47:18,088
Apparently, we're all made of stars.

603
00:47:18,088 --> 00:47:21,424
The earth was born when a star exploded,

604
00:47:21,424 --> 00:47:24,886
and that's how we were created.

605
00:47:24,886 --> 00:47:28,473
We might come from different races and countries,

606
00:47:28,473 --> 00:47:30,725
but ultimately,

607
00:47:30,725 --> 00:47:33,986
we're all made of the same stardust.

608
00:47:36,564 --> 00:47:38,733
That's amazing.

609
00:47:38,733 --> 00:47:40,235
Isn't it?

610
00:47:40,235 --> 00:47:41,869
Yeah.

611
00:47:43,238 --> 00:47:48,702
We're the stars of Inokashira.

612
00:47:48,702 --> 00:47:50,662
"Stars of Inokashira"?

613
00:47:50,662 --> 00:47:52,191
Right.

614
00:47:57,419 --> 00:47:59,295
I promise I'll buy you a Mont Blanc cake

615
00:47:59,295 --> 00:48:01,087
on your next birthday.

616
00:48:01,087 --> 00:48:04,384
Just like your grandma did
when you were younger.

617
00:48:07,220 --> 00:48:09,480
Thank you.

618
00:48:13,476 --> 00:48:17,112
We only spoke of a bright future together.

619
00:48:18,064 --> 00:48:21,151
We went out of our way
to avoid our problems.

620
00:48:21,151 --> 00:48:23,445
And those uncertainties

621
00:48:23,445 --> 00:48:26,364
and the illusions

622
00:48:26,364 --> 00:48:31,494
rolled into a snowball and buried us inside.

623
00:48:31,494 --> 00:48:34,998
We were blind to the harsh realities of the world

624
00:48:34,998 --> 00:48:38,084
when we were at the peak of happiness.

625
00:48:38,084 --> 00:48:40,420
We were nothing but a couple of stars

626
00:48:40,420 --> 00:48:45,349
that were shining ever so naively in love.

627
00:48:50,722 --> 00:48:52,640
[SASAE HIKARI]

628
00:48:52,640 --> 00:48:55,894
Let's take a question
from the livestream this time.

629
00:48:55,894 --> 00:48:59,689
We'll now take a question
from the livestream.

630
00:48:59,689 --> 00:49:02,860
"I've also had a similar experience
to the female protagonist,

631
00:49:02,860 --> 00:49:05,320
so I could easily relate
to the story as I read it.

632
00:49:05,320 --> 00:49:08,656
But in reality, it was incredibly difficult

633
00:49:08,656 --> 00:49:13,203
to overcome borders
and cultural differences with only love.

634
00:49:13,203 --> 00:49:16,581
Do you still believe that that is possible?"

635
00:49:16,581 --> 00:49:19,042
"I had a similar experience
to the female protagonist..."

636
00:49:19,042 --> 00:49:21,628
This is amazing.

637
00:49:21,628 --> 00:49:24,430
I'm so incredibly proud.

638
00:49:29,219 --> 00:49:31,805
If I'm being honest,

639
00:49:31,805 --> 00:49:37,943
I did not write this novel
to deliver an overwhelming message.

640
00:49:39,476 --> 00:49:42,482
"If I'm being honest,
I did not write this novel

641
00:49:42,482 --> 00:49:45,944
to deliver an overwhelming message."

642
00:49:45,944 --> 00:49:48,530
I wrote this story

643
00:49:48,530 --> 00:49:52,075
because of the unforgettable memories
I had for one person

644
00:49:52,075 --> 00:49:55,245
as well as the feeling of regret I had.

645
00:49:55,245 --> 00:49:58,957
It's a recollection of my honest feelings.

646
00:49:58,957 --> 00:50:04,295
If that person happens to read my book,

647
00:50:04,295 --> 00:50:06,003
I hope they understand

648
00:50:06,003 --> 00:50:09,801
that I was young and inexperienced

649
00:50:09,801 --> 00:50:12,221
when we were together.

650
00:50:12,221 --> 00:50:17,434
That was the sliver of hope
I held onto when writing this book.

651
00:50:17,434 --> 00:50:19,227
I see.

652
00:50:19,227 --> 00:50:23,023
The fact that you were
so honest in your writing

653
00:50:23,023 --> 00:50:26,943
must be why so many readers
could empathize with your story.

654
00:50:26,943 --> 00:50:30,822
It seems like we've come to the end
of the book concert portion.

655
00:50:30,822 --> 00:50:33,491
Let's now move on to the book signing.

656
00:50:33,491 --> 00:50:37,495
The signing will take place in five minutes.

657
00:50:37,495 --> 00:50:39,255
Thank you.

658
00:51:04,689 --> 00:51:08,659
